messages.content: 9-1-1, what's your emergency?
530 West Humbleweed Road.
Gilbert Airs on 8.5.233.
530 West Humbleweed and Gilbert, what's going on there?
There were gunshots. My mom, my niece, and my sister are all on the floor. I think they're hurt badly.
You said your mom, your sister, and your niece are on the floor?
Yes, my mom's boyfriend, J.T. Reddy, they were fighting and screaming. I was in my room, and now they're all dead.
Where did you hear the gunshots from?
I heard it coming from outside. The front door is open. They're all lying on the floor, and there's blood.
Who's been shot? Do you know?
My mom, Lisa Maderos. My sister and my niece too.
Your mom, your sister, and your niece have all been shot?
Yes.
Okay. We have officers on the way.
Thank you.
Where is he now?
I don't know. I think he's gone. The front door is open.
Do you know where the gun is?
He has lots of guns in the garage. They were fighting, there was a lot of noise.
Do you think he's in the garage?
I don't know where he is. I think he left.
Does he have a vehicle?
Yes, he has a black car.
What kind of car is it?
It's a four-door passenger car.
Is it registered to him?
Yes, it's registered to him.
What is his name?
J.T. Reddy. Jason Reddy.
Do you know how old he is?
I think he's in his 30s.
Where does he live?
He lives with my mom here.
Where are you now?
I'm in my room.
You said the front door is open, and then what?
Turn right and there's a hallway. My room is down there.
Okay, could I have your name?
Brittany Maderos. B-R-I-T-T-A-N-Y.
Are you injured at all?
No, I'm not injured. I was just sleeping.
Does he know you're in the house?
Yes.
I want you to stay where you are. We have officers on the way. Brittany, you're doing a really good job, okay?
Okay.
Do you have any idea if J.T. is still in the house?
I have no idea.
Are you in your bedroom? Is the door closed?
Yes, it's closed.
What are you wearing?
I'm wearing a red shirt and black shorts.
Do you know what Jason was wearing?
No, I don't know what he was wearing. I haven't seen him all morning.
What does Jason do for a living?
He goes to the border with his friends, but he doesn't work. He just stays at my mom's house.
Does he have any weapons in the house?
Yes, in the garage. I think there's a gun in my mom's room too.
Okay, stay with me. Officers are at your house. Stay where you are until they come in. Brittany, are you listening?
Yes.
Officers are coming into your house. Do not do anything unless I tell you, okay?
Okay.
They're coming into my room now.
Are you talking to officers now?
Yes.
Do you want me to hang up?
I think so.
Okay, I'll let you talk to the officers. Stay safe.
